The paper presents a novel architecture that integrates an RDBMS with neural text mining abilities for entity linking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also heavily relies on natural language processing techniques, such as neural embeddings and similarity functions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper utilizes machine learning libraries, such as TensorFlow, which indicates that it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
